fka/storage/internals/log/LogConfig.java)** provides validation methods for retention configuration:\n\n- **validateBrokerLogConfigValues() (lines 494-500)**: Entry point for broker-level validation that calls remote storage-specific validators when remote log storage is enabled.\n- **validateRemoteStorageRetentionSize() (lines 578-592)**: Validates that when log.retention.bytes is set, the log.local.retention.bytes value is not -1 and does not exceed log.retention.bytes.\n- **validateRemoteStorageRetentionTime() (lines 595-609)**: Validates that when log.retention.ms is set, the log.local.retention.ms value is not -1 and does not exceed log.retention.ms.\n\n## Dynamic Configuration Updates\n\n**DynamicBrokerConfig (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/DynamicBrokerConfig.scala)** handles dynamic configuration changes:\n\n- **validateLogLocalRetentionMs() (lines 664-676)**: Validates changes to log local retention time, ensuring it doesn't exceed log.retention.ms when both are configured.\n- **validateLogLocalRetentionBytes() (lines 679-691)**: Validates changes to log local retention bytes, ensuring it doesn't exceed log.retention.bytes when both are configured.\n\n## Remote Log Manager Integration\n\n**RemoteLogManager (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/log/remote/storage/RemoteLogManager.java)** extends retention enforcement to remote log segments:\n\n- **RemoteLogRetentionHandler inner class (lines 1116-1200)**: Contains the retention checking logic for remote segments.\n- **isSegmentBreachedByRetentionSize() (lines 1131-1152)**: Checks if a remote segment exceeds the size-based retention threshold.\n- **isSegmentBreachedByRetentionTime() (lines 1154-1171)**: Checks if a remote segment exceeds the time-based retention threshold based on the segment's maximum timestamp.\n\n## Configuration Constants\n\n**ServerLogConfigs (server-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/config/ServerLogConfigs.java)** and **RemoteLogManagerConfig (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/log/remote/storage/RemoteLogManagerConfig.java)** define the configuration properties:\n\n- LOG_RETENTION_TIME_MILLIS_CONFIG: Time-based retention threshold in milliseconds\n- LOG_RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG: Size-based retention threshold in bytes\n- LOG_CLEANUP_INTERVAL_MS_CONFIG: Frequency of retention checks (default 300 seconds)\n- LOG_LOCAL_RETENTION_MS_CONFIG: Local retention time for tiered storage\n- LOG_LOCAL_RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG: Local retention bytes for tiered storage\n\nThe entire retention enforcement system is designed to work at both the broker level (affecting all topics) and the topic/partition level (allowing per-topic customization), with special handling for tiered/remote log storage scenarios."
